Key Match Events: Andre Russell got a double strike of Quinton de Kock (12) and Reeza Hendricks (golden duck) in the second over.
Heinrich Klaasen hit a six and three boundaries off Gudakesh Motie in an over that cost the West Indies 20 runs.
Kagiso Rabada took a wicket in the 15.2nd over, leaving South Africa needing 13 runs off the last ten balls.
Marco Jansen hammered Obed McCoy over long-on for six to take South Africa to 124 for seven with five balls to spare.
Miscellaneous Highlights: West Indies struggled for long stretches with the bat and mustered 135 for eight.
Kyle Mayers made 35 off 34 balls as he shared in an 81-run partnership with Roston Chase.
Tabraiz Shamsi, Keshav Maharaj, and Aiden Markram put a stranglehold on the hosts with 57 dot balls.
Andre Russell got a double strike in the second over, boosting the Windies.
South Africa top group II of the Super Eight phase with a perfect six points and keep their unbeaten run in the tourney alive.
West Indies finish the group third on two points.
